rs. Thomas Cooper于大约1355年出生。她于大约1378年与Thomas Cooper在英国英格兰结婚。"},"hr":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"oko 1355.–preminula","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"preminuo","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"preminula","1355–Female":"1355–preminula","Abt 1355":"oko 1355.","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329"},"cs":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"okolo 1355–Zesnulá","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"Zesnulý","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"Zesnulá","1355–Female":"1355–Zesnulá","Abt 1355":"okolo 1355","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329"},"da":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"omkring 1355–Afdød","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"Afdød","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"Afdød","1355–Female":"1355–Afdød","Abt 1355":"omkring 1355","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329"},"nl":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"circa 1355–Overleden","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"Overleden","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"Overleden","1355–Female":"1355–Overleden","Abt 1355":"circa 1355","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329"},"en":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"about 1355–Deceased","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"Deceased","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"Deceased","1355–Female":"1355–Deceased","Abt 1355":"about 1355","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cooper","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: occupational name for a maker and repairer of wooden vessels such as barrels, tubs, buckets, casks, and vats, from Middle English <i>couper</i>, <i>cowper</i> (apparently from Middle Dutch <i>kūper</i>, a derivative of <i>kūp</i> ‘tub, container’, which was borrowed independently into English as <i>coop</i>). The prevalence of the surname, its cognates, and equivalents bears witness to the fact that this was one of the chief specialist trades in the Middle Ages throughout Europe. In North America, the English surname has absorbed some cases of like-sounding cognates from other languages, for example Dutch   Kuiper  .","Americanized form of Jewish (Ashkenazic) <b>Kupfer</b> and <b>Kupper</b> (see   Kuper  ).","Dutch: occupational name for a buyer or merchant, Middle Dutch <i>coper</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Kuiper","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Dutch Gerrit, Hendrik, Willem, Harm, Klaas, Kort, Marinus, Nicolaas, Wouter.","Dutch: occupational name for a cooper, Middle Dutch <i>cup(e)re</i>."]},{"name":"Couper","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Cooper  ."]},{"name":"Hooper","meanings":["English (southwestern): occupational name for a cooper, someone who fitted wooden or metal hoops on wooden casks and barrels, or a barrel-maker, from Middle English <i>hoper</i>, an agent derivative of <i>hop</i> ‘hoop, band’. Compare   Cooper  ."]},{"name":"Coop","meanings":["English (Lancashire): metonymic occupational name for a cooper, from Middle English <i>coupe</i>, <i>cupe</i> ‘tub, cask’ (from Latin <i>cūpa</i>), probably used for a cooper; compare   Cooper  . In some cases the surname may have been derived from a pub or house sign.","Americanized form of German or Dutch   Koop  .","History: It was David Koop (his father's surname also spelled <i>Kupe</i>) from Germany whose surname was changed to <i>Coop</i> after he settled in PA toward the end of the 18th century. He later moved to VA."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Thomas Cooper was born about 1355. She married Thomas Cooper about 1378, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"umbes 1355–Surnud","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"Surnud","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"Surnud","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","Abt 1355":"umbes 1355","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329"},"fi":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"noin 1355–Kuollut","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"Kuollut","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"Kuollut","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","Abt 1355":"noin 1355","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329"},"fr":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"environ 1355–Décédée","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"Décédé","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"Décédée","1355–Female":"1355–Décédée","Abt 1355":"environ 1355","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Thomas Cooper est née environ 1355. Elle a épousé Thomas Cooper environ 1378, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"um 1355–Verstorben","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"Verstorben","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"Verstorben","1355–Female":"1355–Verstorben","Abt 1355":"um 1355","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Thomas Cooper wurde um 1355 geboren. Sie hat um 1378 in England, United Kingdom Thomas Cooper geheiratet."},"ht":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"about 1355–Desede","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"Desede","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"Desede","1355–Female":"1355–Desede","Abt 1355":"about 1355","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329"},"hu":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"1355 körül–elhunyt","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"elhunyt","1370–1441":"1370–1441","–Female":"elhunyt","1355–Female":"1355–elhunyt","Abt 1355":"1355 körül","1355":"1355","1441":"1441","1430":"1430","1370":"1370","1329":"1329"},"id":{"Abt 1355–Deceased":"sekitar 1355–Telah Meninggal","1329–1430":"1329–1430","–Male":"Telah